o you can easily secure your dream domain, at the cheapest possible price.</p><p>Check out <a href="/domain-names/pricing" class="branded underlined">domain pricing page</a> for more details.</p></div></li><li><h3>Can I get discounts when buying domain names in bulk?</h3><div class="content"><p>Absolutely! We'll make sure you get the cheapest domain registration prices possible when buying in bulk.</p><p class="hidden-mobile"><a href="/info/contact" class="branded underlined">Get in touch</a> today to find out exactly how much you could save.</p></div></li><li><h3>How long does it take to buy a domain name?</h3><div class="content"><p>Buying a domain at LCN takes seconds. In most cases, your domain name will be ready to use, by the time it takes you to navigate back to your control panel to use it.</p></div></li><li><h3>What's the maximum period I can buy a domain for?</h3><div class="content"><p>The majority of domain name extensions can be registered for a maximum of 10 years at a time (except .CO which is 5 years). You cannot own a domain “forever”, but you can effectively keep a domain name for as long as you need it by continuing to renew it.</p></div></li><li><h3>What happens when my domain name expires?</h3><div class="content"><p>Forgetting to renew a domain can be a disaster for a business. That’s why we send out renewal reminders 90, 60, 30, 14 and 7 days before the expiry date. You can also choose to receive a free text message 7 days before the expiry date. If your domain does expire, you still have a chance to renew.</p><p>For .uk, .co.uk, .org.uk and .me.uk domains, there is a 90 day ‘grace-period’, whereas most other domains have 30 days. There can be a fee to restore an expired domain, depending on the status of the domain name. The fee depends on the type of extension, which is why we’d always recommend renewing your domain name well in advance of the expiry date.</p></div></li><li><h3>Are all domain names eligible for domain proxy?</h3><div class="content"><p>Domain proxy can be used when you register any .co.uk, .com, .net, .me.uk, .uk, .org.uk or .net.uk domain. We will send your domain registration to the Registry with masked details. For more details on how to add domain proxy to your domains, check out <a href="/support/articles/how-to-hide-your-personal-details-from-the-public-whois-database" class="branded underlined">this support guide</a>.</p></div></li><li><h3>How long is domain proxy free for?</h3><div class="content"><p>The <a href="/domain-names/privacy" class="branded underlined">domain proxy</a> service is free for the first registration term. So, whether you buy a domain for 1, 2, 5, or 10 years, your domain proxy service will be free for the same amount of time.</p></div></li><li><h3>How much does domain proxy cost to renew?</h3><div class="content"><p>The renewal of our domain proxy service is 
